  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HSEQ Officer cum Building Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>HSEQ Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Implement, maintain, and improve <strong>HSEQ programs</strong> in compliance with <strong>Singapore WSH regulations</strong>, <strong>ISO standards</strong>, and company policies.</li><li>Conduct <strong>safety audits, risk assessments, and workplace inspections</strong>.</li><li>Monitor compliance with <strong>HSEQ regulations</strong>, <strong>ISO standards</strong>, and the Company’s <strong>Quality & Safety Management Systems</strong>.</li><li>Investigate incidents, identify <strong>root causes</strong>, and recommend <strong>corrective and preventive actions</strong>.</li><li>Conduct <strong>HSEQ training, toolbox talks, and safety inductions</strong> for employees and contractors.</li><li>Maintain accurate <strong>HSEQ records, reports, and KPIs</strong>.</li></ul><p><strong>Building / Facility Management Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Identify building defects, maintenance needs, and operational issues.</li><li>Engage and coordinate <strong>external contractors</strong> for rectification and maintenance works.</li><li>Ensure contractor works comply with <strong>safety and quality requirements</strong>.</li></ul><p><strong>Combined Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform duties in accordance with <strong>Health, Safety, Environmental, and Quality (HSEQ)</strong> requirements for the role of <strong>HSEQ Officer cum Building Executive</strong>.</li><li>Ensure compliance with <strong>Group Policies and Procedures</strong> and all <strong>applicable statutory and regulatory requirements</strong>.</li><li>Promote a <strong>safe, compliant, and environmentally responsible</strong> workplace culture.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p><strong>Education & Certifications</strong></p><ul><li><strong>SWSHPP / OPISCS Certificate</strong></li><li><strong>Specialist Diploma in Workplace Safety and Health (WSH Level C)</strong> with latest regulatory updates</li></ul><p><strong>Experience & Skills</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Minimum 3–5 years of relevant experience</strong> in HSEQ and/or facility management roles.</li><li>Strong knowledge of <strong>Singapore WSH legislation</strong>, ISO standards, and building safety requirements.</li><li>Good communication, reporting, and organizational skills.</li><li>Proactive, detail-oriented, and able to multitask effectively.</li></ul><p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p><ul><li>Opportunities for <strong>professional development and training</strong></li><li>Dynamic work environment with <strong>career growth potential</strong></li><li>Opportunity to contribute to <strong>safe, compliant, and sustainable workplace practices</strong></li></ul>",
